</taxonomicName>
in (36) dorsal and (37) lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="107" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1743,2020]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1743,1768]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">Discussion.</emphasis>
This species was previously reported from shaded, gravel-bottomed parts of streams in Kanchanaburi, Phetchaburi and Prachuap Khiri Khan provinces (
<bibRefCitation author="Vitheepradit" box="[913,1227,1779,1804]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" refString="Vitheepradit, A. &amp; Sites, R. W. (2007) A review of Ptilomera (Heteroptera: Gerridae) of Thailand with descriptions of three new species. Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 100, 139 - 151." type="journal article" year="2007">
Vitheepradit &amp; Sites 
<number box="[1166,1227,1780,1804]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Most specimens occurred on the water surface on the lee side of emergent rocks in shaded parts of the stream near the margin where there was less turbulence (
<bibRefCitation author="Vitheepradit" box="[455,760,1851,1876]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" refString="Vitheepradit, A. &amp; Sites, R. W. (2007) A review of Ptilomera (Heteroptera: Gerridae) of Thailand with descriptions of three new species. Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 100, 139 - 151." type="journal article" year="2007">
Vitheepradit &amp; Sites 
<number box="[699,760,1852,1876]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). When they were pursued, they tended to swim upstream; however, they seemed not to be able to skate on the water surface as well as did 
<taxonomicName authority="Vitheepradit &amp; Sites 2007" authorityName="Vitheepradit &amp; Sites" authorityYear="2007" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Ptilomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tigrina">
<emphasis box="[1080,1094,1888,1911]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1109,1185,1888,1911]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">tigrina</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Vitheepradit" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" refString="Vitheepradit, A. &amp; Sites, R. W. (2007) A review of Ptilomera (Heteroptera: Gerridae) of Thailand with descriptions of three new species. Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 100, 139 - 151." type="journal article" year="2007">
Vitheepradit &amp; Sites 
<number box="[151,212,1924,1948]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Moreover, they appeared to return to occupy the same place they were before they were pursued (
<bibRefCitation author="Vitheepradit" box="[158,466,1959,1984]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" refString="Vitheepradit, A. &amp; Sites, R. W. (2007) A review of Ptilomera (Heteroptera: Gerridae) of Thailand with descriptions of three new species. Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 100, 139 - 151." type="journal article" year="2007">
Vitheepradit &amp; Sites 
<number box="[405,466,1960,1984]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[488,594,1960,1983]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">P. j a r i y a e</emphasis>
can be distinguished in the field by its reddish brown color, whereas 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Ptilomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tigrina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">P. tigrina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is relatively dark brown, and 
<taxonomicName box="[562,668,1996,2019]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Ptilomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jariyae">
<emphasis box="[562,668,1996,2019]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">P. jariyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seemed to be much less abundant than was 
<taxonomicName box="[1163,1266,1996,2019]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Ptilomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tigrina">
<emphasis box="[1163,1266,1996,2019]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">P. tigrina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
